<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12166b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12166b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12166b"> 166(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> lefthandwise</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Legend of Patricks Contest with the Druids]</font> Suddenly the company assembled at Tara saw a light shining across the plain of Breg from the hill of Slane. King Loigaire, in surprise and alarm, consulted his magicians, and they said, &ldquo;O king, unless this fire which you see be quenched this same night, it will never be quenched; and the kindler of it will overcome us all and seduce all the folk of your realm.&rdquo; And the king replied, &ldquo;It shall not be. but we will go to see the issue of the matter, and we will put to death those who do such sin against our kingdom.&rdquo; So he had nine chariots yoked, and, with the queen and his two chief sorcerers and others, he drove through the night over the plain of Breg. And in order to win magic power over them who had kindled the fire, they wheeled <mark>lefthandwise</mark>, or contrariwise to the sun&apos;s course. <small> J.B. Bury, <a name="JBSP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JBSP"><cite title="source">Life of Saint Patrick</cite></a> (1905) 104-5</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
